NAIVETTE, Incorporated, v. The PHILAD COMPANY et al. No. 7661. Circuit Court of Appeals, Sixth Circuit. Dec. 8, 1937. Maurice S. Cayne, of Chicago, 111., and Kwis, Hudson & Kent, of Cleveland, Ohio, for appellant. Morris Kirschstein, of New York City, and Hull, Brock & West, of Cleveland, Ohio, for appellees.

Before MOORMAN, HICKS, and SIMONS, Circuit Judges.

PER CURIAM.

It is ordered that the appeal Jn this cause be and same is dismissed, pursuant to stipulation of counsel.
